  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expanding the EQuIP diagnostics toolkit</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EQuIP toolkit serves to independently undertake thorough industrial diagnostics and to formulate industrial policy strategies that are sufficiently evidence-based. The current EQuIP diagnostics toolkit (EQuIP 1), however, lacks depth on some important dimensions of industrial development. On the economic dimension, EQuIP 1 shows a strong emphasis on product innovation but does not yet allow an assessment of process innovations, i.e. the capacity of industrial sectors to upgrade through innovation or, on the other hand, the risk of destroying jobs through modern process technologies. On the environmental dimension, EQuIP 1 needs further indicators on climate change. On the inclusiveness dimension, EQuIP 1 warrants a deeper look at questions of gender- and income inequality.</narrative>
  </description>
